item.description: Abstract Sequential Abstract Sequential Stephanie Hobson's abstract thoughts in the sequence she has them. On 2018-01-19. I was once compared to a striped carrot, a potion of beguiling, a saffron crayon and the Batmobile by a group of university friends while in Quebec City drinking some very cheep wine because it comes in bottles that make pretty beach glass. I got an education, a career, and a house but it turns out that doesn’t necessarily lead to happiness… so now I’m trying other things.
